{
  "texts": [
    "While GPT3.5 was able to produce a response in approximately 5 seconds, Llama2 13B required nearly 30 seconds to 1 minute depending on the complexity of the query, with our available computational resources.When using an externally hosted model it is imperative that data privacy be considered, since prompts to a language model from our students can be classified as confidential student information.",
    "We used two strategies to ensure data privacy, and specifically to ensure that no prompt could be traced back to a specific student:1.",
    "Students were not able to log in, nor were they able to provide any personal information unless they did so in the prompt itself.",
    "Therefore, all prompts are sent from a single, organizational account, and not linked to any student. 2.",
    "We interfaced with GPT3.5 via the OpenAI Python API."
  ]
}